  "prompt": "Do Kit Kat bars have peanut ingredients?",
  "response": "Standard Kit Kat bars do not contain peanut ingredients. The classic Kit Kat ingredients typically include sugar, wheat flour, cocoa butter, nonfat milk, chocolate, refined palm kernel oil, and milk fat, among others. However, they are produced in facilities that may also process peanuts, so there could be a risk of cross-contamination.\n\nIf you have a peanut allergy, it's always a good idea to check the packaging for specific allergen information or contact the manufacturer directly to ensure the product is safe for you to consume. Additionally, some flavored or specialty Kit Kat varieties might have different ingredients, so always read the label carefully.",
